      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "CADENCE LANE (4) led last time out and was successful for the first time this campaign at Gawler over 2070m, getting home by 10 metres. Meets some better types this time but another big run is on the cards. DAISY BOUCHEA (7) missed the placings two runs back then did a great job to finish 9 metres back in third despite breaking after interference in the run over 2070m at Gawler four days ago. It doesn't get any easier but she is going well enough to take this out. BEWARE THE FURY (10) is the next elect off a last-start win by 2.75 metres at Globe Derby Park over 2230m. THE VICARS GIRL (6) has been about the mark of late and must be respected, the latest offering a sound second at Gawler over 2070m.",
